parties.raw_snippet: This Master Agreement is made as of the 26 day of January, 2007 (the “Effective Date”), by and between Oriental Financial Group Inc., a Puerto Rico financial holding company (“Customer”), and Metavante Corporation, a Wisconsin corporation (“Metavante”).
parties.reasoning: The opening paragraph of the agreement explicitly names the two contracting entities and labels their roles (Customer and Metavante). This identifies the primary parties to the contract.

contract_type.reasoning: The title at the top of the document and the substance (Metavante providing technology services and licenses to Customer) indicate this is an outsourcing arrangement for technology/services.

notice_period.raw_snippet: Metavante shall provide a written renewal notice to Customer at least twelve (12) months prior to the expiration of the Initial Term (the “Renewal Notice”). Unless Customer notifies Metavante of its intent not to renew this Agreement in writing within a period of three (3) months following the Renewal Notice, this Agreement shall automatically renew at the end of the Initial Term on the same terms (including pricing terms) for one (1) twelve-month period.
notice_period.reasoning: Section 2.1 sets out the automatic renewal process: Metavante gives a Renewal Notice at least 12 months prior, and Customer must notify Metavante of intent not to renew within three (3) months following that Renewal Notice to prevent automatic renewal. The required notice to prevent renewal is the three-month window following the Renewal Notice.

expiration_date.raw_snippet: The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and end on November 30, 2014 (the “Initial Term”).
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 4 (and earlier summary) explicitly states the term commences on the Effective Date and ends on a calendar date: November 30, 2014, which is the contract expiration of the Initial Term.

renewal_term.raw_snippet: Unless Customer notifies Metavante of its intent not to renew this Agreement in writing within a period of three (3) months following the Renewal Notice, this Agreement shall automatically renew at the end of the Initial Term on the same terms (including pricing terms) for one (1) twelve-month period.
renewal_term.reasoning: Section 2.1 specifies the automatic renewal duration: if not timely declined, the Agreement automatically renews 'for one (1) twelve-month period' on the same terms.

agreement_date.raw_snippet: This Master Agreement is made as of the 26 day of January, 2007 (the “Effective Date”), by and between Oriental Financial Group Inc., a Puerto Rico financial holding company (“Customer”), and Metavante Corporation, a Wisconsin corporation (“Metavante”).
agreement_date.reasoning: The contract states 'This Master Agreement is made as of the 26 day of January, 2007' which is the signing/made date of the agreement.

effective_date.raw_snippet: This Master Agreement is made as of the 26 day of January, 2007 (the “Effective Date”), by and between Oriental Financial Group Inc., a Puerto Rico financial holding company (“Customer”), and Metavante Corporation, a Wisconsin corporation (“Metavante”).
effective_date.reasoning: The same clause defines the date (26 day of January, 2007) as the “Effective Date.” Therefore the effective date equals the agreement date.

governing_law.raw_snippet: 17.1. Governing Law. The validity, construction and interpretation of this Agreement and the rights and duties of the parties hereto shall be governed by the internal laws of the State of New York, excluding its principles of conflict of laws.
governing_law.reasoning: Section 17.1 is the governing law clause and names the State whose internal laws govern the agreement.
